						               													<description>Dice and Daggers is a simple, fast, and friendly(ish) &amp;ndash; or not &amp;ndash; dice game. In Dice and Daggers, players attempt to reach 20 gold before everyone else without being knocked out of the game. On a turn, the active player rolls three dice, then chooses two of them, with the other players taking the action on the remaining die. When you roll three-of-a-kind, something good happens!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The dice have five symbols on them:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Coins: The player gains 1 coin.&amp;#10;    Crown: The player draws 1 card.&amp;#10;    Dagger: The player either discards a shield or takes 1 damage.&amp;#10;    Shield: The player takes a shield token, which can later block a dagger.&amp;#10;    Thief: The active player must choose this die, although it grants no actions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Let's say the active player rolls Coin, Shield, Crown. If he chooses the coin and the shield, he receives 1 coin and a shield to protect himself in the future should he roll a dagger (or be forced to choose the dagger). The other players each draw 1 card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dice and Daggers includes rules for five different ways to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
